  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I reduce lips protrusion without surgery?",
  "response": "Reducing lip protrusion without surgery can be achieved through a combination of non-invasive methods, including orthodontic treatments, lifestyle changes, and facial exercises. Here are some approaches you can consider:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Orthodontic Treatment**\n   - **Braces or Clear Aligners**: Misaligned teeth or improper jaw positioning can contribute to lip protrusion. Orthodontic treatment can help reposition the teeth and jaw, which may reduce lip prominence.\n   - **Retainers**: In some cases, retainers can be used to correct mild protrusion after orthodontic treatment.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Facial Exercises**\n   - Strengthening and toning the muscles around the mouth and jawline can help reduce the appearance of protrusion.\n   - **Lip Pucker Exercise**: Pucker your lips and hold for 5 seconds, then relax. Repeat 10\u201315 times daily.\n   - **Cheek Puff Exercise**: Fill your cheeks with air, hold for 5 seconds, and release. Repeat 10\u201315 times daily.\n   - **Smile Exercise**: Smile as wide as possible, hold for 5 seconds, and relax. Repeat 10\u201315 times daily.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Proper Posture**\n   - Poor posture, especially forward head posture, can make lip protrusion more noticeable. Practice good posture by aligning your head, neck, and spine.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Weight Management**\n   - Excess fat in the face and neck can contribute to the appearance of lip protrusion. Maintaining a healthy weight through diet and exercise may help reduce facial fat.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Dermal Fillers**\n   - While this is a non-surgical procedure, dermal fillers can be used to balance the appearance of the lips by adding volume to other areas of the face, reducing the focus on lip protrusion.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Lifestyle Changes**\n   - Avoid habits like thumb-sucking, lip-biting, or excessive use of straws, which can contribute to protrusion over time.\n   - Stay hydrated to maintain healthy skin and muscle tone.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Consult a Specialist**\n   - Visit an orthodontist or maxillofacial specialist to assess the cause of lip protrusion. They can recommend the most effective non-surgical treatment plan tailored to your needs.\n\n---\n\nWhile these methods can help reduce the appearance of lip protrusion, results may vary depending on the underlying cause. For significant protrusion, surgical options like lip reduction or orthognathic surgery may be recommended. Always consult a professional before starting any treatment.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
